caption: Also known as [em2]Protium[em2] this is most abundant form of[br]Hydrogen in the universe. As just a single proton (with[br]a single electron) this is the simplest type of element[br]and accounts for about 75% of all atoms in the entire[br]universe.

This form of Carbon is used as the standard for setting[br]the masses of all other atomic nuclei. Its atomic mass[br]is exactly 12 by definition. With an abundance of 98.89%[br]of all Carbon in the universe this also the most common[br]form of Carbon by far.
